# Feature Architecture

## Folder layout

```
src/
  app/                  # Routes only — thin RSC pages, layouts, loading, api/
  feature/<name>/       # Business UI + logic
    components/         # Feature components
    views/              # Page-level client compositions (*View)
    hooks/ | hook/      # Feature hooks
    contexts/           # Feature React context
    data/               # Constants, static config
    lib/                # Feature helpers (nuqs params, etc.)
    utils/              # Pure helpers
  components/ui/        # shadcn primitives — no business logic
  components/           # Shared app components (PageHeader, etc.)
  hooks/                # Shared hooks (use-app-form)
  lib/                  # Infra (db, env, utils, clients)
  trpc/                 # Routers, client, server prefetch helpers
```

## Rules

- `app/` pages are Server Components: parse params, set metadata, `prefetch`, wrap in `HydrateClient`, render a feature `*View`.
- Feature logic lives in `feature/<name>/` — never in `components/ui/`.
- Imports use `@/src/...`.
- Files: `kebab-case.tsx` for components/views; hooks: `use-*.ts`.
- Add `"use client"` only when the file needs hooks, browser APIs, or events.
- Server-only modules: `import "server-only"`.
